QUESTION:In Cangjie code language,How is the subtype relationship established through class inheritance in Cangjie?
ANSWER:When a class inherits from another class, the subclass becomes a subtype of the superclass. This means that an instance of the subclass can be used wherever an instance of the superclass is expected.open class Super { }
class Sub <: Super { }

QUESTION:In Cangjie code language,How is the subtype relationship established through interface implementation in Cangjie?
ANSWER:When a type implements an interface, it becomes a subtype of that interface. This means that an instance of the implementing type can be used wherever an instance of the interface is expected.interface I1 { }
interface I2 { }
interface I3 <: I1 & I2 { }
class C <: I1 { }
extend Int64 <: I2 { }

